			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A charmed (or dire charmed) pet is not at all like a summoned pet. Charming has inherent risk vs reward issues, caps based on finding a suitable mob, penalties for inattentiveness to the pet if it is dispelled or breaks charm, major agro to the charmer, potential to have two mobs very upset with you (the one you are beating on, and the pet that just broke charm), your death causing a major change in teh fight dynamic (your group is suddenly short of a member, while the mobs just gained one add from the now broken pet which is very pissy with everyone), and inability to zone with charmed pets.
<br />

<br />
If a DC pet dies, its gone and you have to start all over ... wait for DC ability to pop up, find suitable pet, etc.
<br />

<br />
The pets are totally different, and its fine to balance them separately.
<br />

<br />
That said, mage pets shouldn't be substantially behind a DC pet for damage output so that a DC class is prefered. But, summoned pets are risk free.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
