			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>danille wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Dabrighter2 wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Please adjust the rain section to request that rains be focused by something.  Either Improved Damage or the DoT focus.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
It already is Dabrighter2. Open the link to Xalmat's detail and read the very bottom section recomendations.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Yes, but I don't want them to have to read the link to learn that rains are not focused by anything and thus becoming useless.  I want it in plain sight so it is harder to ignore.  
<br />

<br />
I also agree resists need to be looked at.  During my 50's I used Sircoo a lot.  {Back then I was an active Pet Canni and mana efficiency was not an issure, just DPS.  As long as two rains hit, Sircoo was the big winner in DPS}  I have liked using them and want to keep using them.  Back then, they were the DPS leader as long at least 2 waves landed and the DPM leader if all three waves landed.  Once I got into the 60's, the rains are not enough better DPS or DPM even if all three waves hit than FBoT to even make me risk using them over FBoT.  I would never use a rain over FBoT unless against high FR mobs.  
<br />

<br />
Yesterday, I was hunting genoids in Wakening Lands for gems for 8th shawl request.  About 1/4 of the mobs were LB to my 65 mage.  Since they were highly fire resisitant, I was using my Magic Based spells.  I used the following pattern, annul {To get rid of sow and other buffs from the shaman genoids.}, Malosini, MoT, Black Steel and depending on resists of MoT, another BS or two.  During this time, my two-boxed cleric was casting Judgement, Mark of Retribution, Judgement, and depending on number of resists of MoT, another Judgement.  
<br />

<br />
Because rains have extra resists, I use the following system to determine wheter to use a rain or not.  If a mob resists 2 or 3 waves, I don't cast a rain on it again.  I also keep a RAIN NUMBER {RN}.  For rains with 0 resists, I add one to the RN.  For rains with 1 resist, I add 0 to the RN.  For rains with 2 resists, I subtract 1 from the RN, for rains with 3 resists, I subtract 2 from the RN.  If the RN continues to increase, most the rains are hitting and rains are effective.  If the RN stays about the same, mostly one wave is being resisted, FBoT is better DPS and DPM.  {During the 50's. it meant your DPS was a little better and DPM was a little worse.}  A RN that is decreasing means drop that rain now, it is getting resisted way too much.  
<br />

<br />
During the first 2 hours I used rains and my RN got as high as 13 and as low as -3.  My most common number of resists was 1, followed by 0, then 2, and finally 3.  Normally I would have switched to FBoT much quicker but the mobs were highly FR and Black Steel is not one of our highest DPS spells so I stuck with MoT.  
<br />

<br />
At about the 2 hour mark, a second <span style="font-weight: bold">LB</span> mob resisted all three waves and I said enough is enough and quit using MoT.  During this time, my cleric never had a resist on his Mark of Retribution or a full resist on his Judgement spell  {May have had partials, but are a different color and I would not necessarly notice.}  so I decided to test not casting Malosini.  My mage now casted annul and then chained BS.  Once I made this change on my mage, my cleric never once casted the third judgement so the Mage's DPS had to go way up.  Additionally, I never had to stop pulling because my mage got low on mana as I had to do several times while using MoT so my DPM had to go up to as well.  
<br />

<br />
If someone had told me that you would get better DPS and DPM by using Blace Steel over MoT, I would not have believed it.  Some things you must experience for yourself.  If you can't effectively use rains against low DB and LB mobs, when can you effectivetly use rains?  As it stands today, never. Rains, another tool for farming greens put pretty much useless for any real application.<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
<br />
